values.text: Sorry, I didn't understand that.
I do understand questions about outstanding verifications on a case or client, or about caseworker procedures.
Type or choose an option to continue.
You can ask me about caseworker procedures, for example, how to add new income or address evidence for a client. If at any stage you want to start again click on the question mark below.

generic.title: Type a question or select an option.

values.text: Complete these steps to add income evidence.
1. Go to the Dashboard page in the evidence workspace.
2. Select to create Income evidence.
3. Enter the values for the new income evidence.
4. Select Save.
5. Select Apply Changes from the action menu in the evidence workspace.

After you add your evidence you may need to verify it, or if the client is a member of other cases the evidence may have been shared to other cases that you manage and may require manual review and processing.

generic.title: If you want to see all Job Aids in relation to caseworker procedure and processes, see caseworker job aids
What type of evidence do you want to add?
Check the details and try again, or choose another option.

values.text: Complete the following steps to add proof for an outstanding verification. For example, to add proof for income.
1. From the case, click the Evidence tab to open the evidence workspace.
2. Click the Verifications page and click Outstanding verifications.
3. Expand the verification record for the evidence type to see the details.
4. Click Add Proof from the row-level action menu.
5. Click an item from the list of acceptable proofs for income evidence
6. Enter the details of the proof and click Save.
Great to chat to you,
If you need anything else let me know.
talk soon!
Complete these steps to add Address Evidence.
1. Go to the Dashboard page in the evidence workspace.
2. Click to create Address evidence.
3. Click the one-to-many case members to whom the new address applies.
4. Enter the new Address details.
5. Click Save and Next.
6. If there is existing address evidence, click the record to end-date.
7. Click Finish.
8. Click Apply Changes from the action menu in the evidence workspace.

generic.title: After you add your evidence you may need to verify it, or if the client is a member of other cases the evidence may have been shared to other cases that you manage and may require manual review and processing.

values.text: Check the details and try again, or choose another option.
What's the case number?
Ok, let's start again, type or choose an option to continue.
Complete the following steps to process incoming evidence.
1. Go to Inbox.
2. Click Available tasks under the task shortcuts menu item.
3. Select the 'New Incoming Evidence on the Case xxx that needs to be resolved' task.
4. Click the Resolve Incoming Evidence primary action to go to the evidence workspace.
5. An informational message is displayed in the evidence workspace indicating that 'There is incoming evidence on this case. Please review and decide if the evidence should be accepted or rejected.'
6. Navigate to the Incoming Evidence page.
7. Expand the incoming Income evidence record to view the Evidence Comparison page.
8. Click the Add as New button on the Incoming Evidence side of the page.

generic.title: After you share evidence across cases, you might want to add more evidence or edit existing evidence.

values.text: I'm here to help you with your caseworker tasks.
I’m currently learning about outstanding verifications on a case or client, and about caseworker procedures.
You can choose an option, or type an identification number, plus text like case, client, ssn, driver, license, or passport, to see verifications.
You can also ask me about caseworker procedures, for example, how to add new income or address evidence for a client. Simply type add income or add address to skip the options.
You can use Ctrl+F to find specific text in my responses.
Type or select an option to continue.

values.text: Which identification number do you want to use?

You're welcome, talk soon!
Complete the following steps to edit evidence.
1. Go to the Active Evidence page in the Evidence Workspace.
2. Click to Edit the active evidence that you want to change over time.
3. Click a Change Reason.
4. If the evidence can change over time, enter the date that you want the evidence change to become effective from in the Effective Date of Change field.
5. Change any values that are effective from the new date.
6. Click Save.
7. Click Apply Changes from the action menu in the Evidence Workspace.
After you edit evidence, you might need to verify it.
Please check the client's details and try again.
